		</font>
		<hr size="1">Recently, a friend of mine, has logged onto eq, only to find a problem that every player dreads, all of his items where missing.  He logged onto his main character, and checked to be sure.  Sure enough, everything was gone.  This happened over Christmas vacation, so he was unable to contact a GM.  He was not too worried, because the same thing had happened to my other friend, but he was able to recover his items.  So anyways, yesterday, when i logged on in the evening, my friend came up to me and said "the gm says u stole my stuff." He is normally one to make jokes, so i laughed it off.  Within a minute, I read "you have been summoned by the gods."  Well for any of you, who have ever been summoned, this is very scary.  I was talking to the GM, whos name will remain unsaid, also claimed that i had stolen his itmes.  Well this supprised me a little, considering i was still completely broke, but i listened on.  Supposedly, i had gone onto a different character on my account, and picked his stuff up, off of the ground.  From there, i "supposedly" gave them to another friend, who then " supposedly" gave them to another friend. where they were finally retrieved by the GM.  The reason i am confused is, not only did the Gm's story change as she contacted each one of us individually, but none of us, had actually done anything.  So in the end the GM decided to suspend the account of the person who lost is stuff, my account, and the final person who had the stuff.  Not the middle player.   If you ask me, it seems a bit weird.  The reason i posted this, was not to complain, for i very much love everquest, but infact to warn all of you of my fate.  I can Guarantee you that i never did anything, and also that none of my fellow friends did anything, but it is a possibility, that someone went onto our accounts.  I dont blame the GM, becuase they were just following there guide lines for the situation, but it does seem strange.  Just wanted to give you all a friendly warning, and to whoever did this to us, I hope that you are caught and banned, before you can do this to anyone else.  Just a warning.  Good luck to all =0)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
